# Security Rules

## Secrets
- All secrets in env vars or `config.yaml` (gitignored)
- Never commit API keys, tokens, passwords
- Use `${ENV_VAR}` syntax in YAML for env expansion
- `.gitignore` must include `config.yaml`, `*.db`, `data/`

## Executor Sandboxing
- All executor agent commands run inside Docker containers
- Containers must have: CPU limit, memory limit, network disabled, read-only root
- Timeout on every execution (default 30s)
- No `--privileged` or `--cap-add` unless explicitly approved

## Approval Gates (HITL)
- Destructive operations require human approval via Telegram
- Approval flow: agent requests → gateway sends approval prompt → user responds
- Timeout on approvals (5 min default) — auto-deny on expiry
- Log every approval decision (approved/denied/expired)
